news.summary:
japan has for the first time deployed a military contingent to the philippines for the “balikatan 2026” drills 🇯🇵🇵🇭🇺🇸

japan became the third-largest participant after the united states and the philippines.

the contingent includes:
- around 1,400 personnel;
- the helicopter carrier js ise, one of japan’s largest warships;
- the landing ship js shimokita;
- the destroyer js ikazuchi;
- transport aircraft c-130h hercules; 
- type 88 anti-ship missile systems.

this marks japan’s first large-scale deployment of combat units since the 2025 mutual access agreement between tokyo and manila came into force. previously, the japan self-defense forces had only participated as observers or in limited humanitarian missions.

other than japan, this year’s exercises will include combat troops from australia, canADA, france, and new zealand. in total, over 17,000 troops will take part in the “balikatan 2026” military drills.

the exercises are scheduled to take place from april 20 to may 8.
